## Pass by Reference
C is pass-by-value by default. Use pointers to modify variables in functions.

```c
void swap(int *a, int *b) {
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;
}

int main() {
    int x = 10, y = 20;
    swap(&x, &y);
    printf("%d %d
", x, y);  // 20 10
}
```

