## Safe Pointer Usage

```c
int *ptr = NULL;  // Points to nothing

// Always check before dereferencing!
if (ptr != NULL) {
    printf("%d
", *ptr);
} else {
    printf("Pointer is NULL!
");
}

// After freeing memory
free(ptr);
ptr = NULL;  // Prevent dangling pointer
```

**Never dereference a NULL pointer!** It causes a segfault.

