## Grouping Variables
A `struct` in C is like a dictionary or a class without methods. It groups related variables under one name.

A `union` is similar, but all variables share the *same* memory location. You can only use one of them at a time, saving memory.

```c
struct Player {
    int hp;
    int score;
};
```
